He has to speak in Munich on Thursday

6
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:54,856
Impossible,no public appearances 
for at least 10 days

7
00:01:54,898 --> 00:01:56,316
I'd  thought you'd say that

8
00:01:56,316 --> 00:01:57,342
He won't listen to us

9
00:01:57,426 --> 00:01:59,277
Has the heat turned up,
the rooms like an oven

10
00:01:59,335 --> 00:02:01,663
-Just what I was going to say
-Exactly what I did say

11
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:04,708
-Well,Heil Hitler!
-Heil Hitler-Heil Hitler

12
00:02:06,636 --> 00:02:07,677
Herr Roeder

13
00:02:08,938 --> 00:02:10,339
There you are,Rabenau

14
00:02:12,207 --> 00:02:14,618
I suppose you're going to tell 
me he can't speak on Thursday

15
00:02:14,718 --> 00:02:16,586
If he does,I won't answer 
for the consequences

16
00:02:16,586 --> 00:02:20,015
I knew it,now Goering and 
Goebbels will both want to deputize

17
00:02:20,048 --> 00:02:21,048
Why not a duet?

18
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:23,310
I'm afraid there might be 
a little lacking in harmony

19
00:02:24,111 --> 00:02:25,187
Good bye

20
00:02:25,212 --> 00:02:27,981
BTW I haven't seen you since 
your wedding,my congratulations

21
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:28,981
Thank you

22
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:31,068
Ought to be some restrictions 
on you Austrians

23
00:02:31,068 --> 00:02:32,944
carrying off all the beauty of Berlin

24
00:02:32,953 --> 00:02:33,953
More restrictions

25
00:02:34,580 --> 00:02:38,325
What can a poor Prussian policeman 
hope to do against your fatal charm?

26
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,327
Why not use your powers of arrest?

27
00:02:43,372 --> 00:02:45,499
-Remember me to Irena,won't you?
-Yes I will

28
00:02:46,767 --> 00:02:47,825
Open

29
00:02:50,137 --> 00:02:51,963
Yes,that's a little inflamed

30
00:02:52,706 --> 00:02:53,799
Say A

31
00:02:53,849 --> 00:02:54,883
A

32
00:02:54,883 --> 00:02:57,761
-Again
-Ninety nine

33
00:02:59,930 --> 00:03:02,724
I'd have you know my other patients 
treat with me with some respect

34
00:03:02,783 --> 00:03:05,644
They are not married to you,
darling,at least I hope they are not

35
00:03:05,928 --> 00:03:08,980
Seriously you can't afford to take 
chances now you're in rehearsal

36
00:03:09,740 --> 00:03:11,942
I've just been telling that 
to another celebrity

37
00:03:11,942 --> 00:03:12,942
Who?

38
00:03:13,001 --> 00:03:14,987
Sc ch,we are indisposed

39
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:16,947
Oh dear,I hope it's nothing serious?

40
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:20,242
He has what it's called 
laryngismus stridulus

41
00:03:20,242 --> 00:03:22,077
My goodness what it's first name?

42
00:03:22,586 --> 00:03:24,287
If you had it,it would be a sore throat

43
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:26,707
Oh,darling you are silly

44
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:30,711
-Otto!
-Irena

45
00:03:30,711 --> 00:03:31,711
Darling!

46
00:03:32,413 --> 00:03:34,339
I thought you were not 
arriving until tomorrow

47
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:36,425
Hello Otto,what sort of 
time did you have in Italy?

48
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:37,475
Marvelous,thanks

49
00:03:37,884 --> 00:03:40,137
What do you got there? A prix de Rome?

50
00:03:40,137 --> 00:03:41,417
No,I just missed it

51
00:03:41,555 --> 00:03:43,031
Well,lets have a look at them anyway

52
00:03:49,530 --> 00:03:51,064
Oh,that's delightful

53
00:03:51,949 --> 00:03:53,734
Isn't that cow rather anemic?

54
00:03:53,734 --> 00:03:55,694
Speaking as a throat specialist or a vet?

55
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:59,656
Rebuffed again,I'd just had 
one from Mrs Roeder

56
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:00,699
Done you good,darling

57
00:04:00,716 --> 00:04:01,908
Thank you very much

58
00:04:03,126 --> 00:04:05,203
Now then,now then,time you're off

59
00:04:05,203 --> 00:04:07,164
Hello Mr Otto,glad to see you back

60
00:04:07,164 --> 00:04:09,124
Now don't you forget 
you've got two calls to make

61
00:04:09,124 --> 00:04:10,167
before you go to your club

62
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:11,852
there's your coat and there's your flower

63
00:04:11,852 --> 00:04:12,852
Thank you

64
00:04:13,028 --> 00:04:15,255
That club,why has it be tonight

65
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,506
It's only once a year,my sweet

66
00:04:16,857 --> 00:04:18,717
I'll be back to see 
the new year in with you

67
00:04:21,336 --> 00:04:22,387
You stay,won't you Otto?

68
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:23,413
I'd love to

69
00:04:23,413 --> 00:04:25,431
I want to make the final 
diagnosis of that cow

70
00:04:25,457 --> 00:04:26,457
Karl

71
00:04:26,809 --> 00:04:27,901
Your flower

72
00:04:29,736 --> 00:04:31,980
One day I'll come and spy on you

73
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,607
You'd be bored to death

74
00:04:33,607 --> 00:04:36,026
we just sit round talking rather pompously

75
00:04:36,026 --> 00:04:37,986
trying to pretend we 
are still at Heidelberg

76
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:40,447
That's what you tell your wives

77
00:04:45,043 --> 00:04:46,119
Tell me about your work

78
00:04:47,237 --> 00:04:48,330
Oh,what are you looking at?

79
00:04:49,415 --> 00:04:51,892
I had to watch that sort of 
thing the whole time out in Italy

80
00:04:52,393 --> 00:04:54,069
Well,do watching now darling

81
00:04:54,169 --> 00:04:55,420
You can do it

82
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:56,460
Suppose I shall

83
00:04:58,532 --> 00:04:59,925
I shall be rather silly

84
00:04:59,958 --> 00:05:01,426
Probably make you very fit

85
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:03,261
Get rid a little of this

86
00:05:11,678 --> 00:05:13,522
I must say they do look rather good

87
00:05:29,371 --> 00:05:32,165
One,two,three,four,five,six,
seven only eight tonight,Sebastian

88
00:05:32,249 --> 00:05:33,249
Yes,Sir

89
00:05:33,366 --> 00:05:34,366
Large Muencher, please

90
00:05:34,835 --> 00:05:36,702
Hello Franz,hello Josef

91
00:05:36,754 --> 00:05:37,954
Wonderful platform for workmen

92
00:05:38,088 --> 00:05:40,924
No unemployment, all you see it's 
what's in front of your face

93
00:05:40,924 --> 00:05:41,924
Hello Karl

94
00:05:42,050 --> 00:05:43,730
-Hello Heini
-Hello Karl

95
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,345
No,no, you need know the rules

96
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:47,031
no politics,isn't it so,Karl?

97
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:49,766
Absolutely,you should do as 
I do leave politics to politicians

98
00:05:49,775 --> 00:05:51,193
There you are,what did I tell you

99
00:05:51,217 --> 00:05:52,419
-Your,beer,Sir
-Thanks

100
00:05:52,561 --> 00:05:54,437
-Telephone,Sir
-Thank you

101
00:05:55,188 --> 00:05:57,190
Well,I leave him to you

102
00:05:57,307 --> 00:05:58,525
It's all very well he's joking

103
00:05:58,525 --> 00:06:01,027
Why is it that bad comedians 
are gloomy on the stage

104
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:04,489
and good comedians,like 
you my dear Emil, are gloomier

105
00:06:05,165 --> 00:06:08,785
Karl,I'm just telling Franz 
how I got this,you remember?

106
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:10,453
I remember yours most attractive

107
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:11,453
Karl,gruss

108
00:06:11,546 --> 00:06:13,748
-Hello,Karl
-Hello Rudolf

109
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:15,592
When did you get back? 
What was America like?

110
00:06:15,684 --> 00:06:17,085
I don't know I went to New York

111
00:06:17,961 --> 00:06:19,921
No need to ask if married life suits you

112
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:21,715
Heavens,this is as obvious as all that

113
00:06:21,715 --> 00:06:23,425
Nothing could have pleased me better

114
00:06:25,952 --> 00:06:27,012
Hello,Father

115
00:06:27,429 --> 00:06:30,473
-Beer?
-Well,just a large one

116
00:06:30,491 --> 00:06:31,566
Sebastian

117
00:06:31,659 --> 00:06:32,659
Gustav

118
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:35,478
Ah Rudolf,excuse me one moment

119
00:06:36,062 --> 00:06:38,231
Well,how are you after 
your American triumphs?

120
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:39,523
Hello,Father

121
00:06:40,125 --> 00:06:42,903
Isn't it extraordinary always 
bottom of the class

122
00:06:42,903 --> 00:06:45,447
Now look at him lightning a 3 mark cigar

123
00:06:45,447 --> 00:06:48,366
Yes,you remember he never 
could do a simple equation

124
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:51,995
and now he can make a million 
vanish right under your eyes

125
00:06:51,995 --> 00:06:53,596
Can you never know what's happen to it

126
00:06:53,922 --> 00:06:57,208
High finance and mathematics,
Father,have nothing in common

127
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:59,085
Judging by your record it certainly haven't

128
00:07:00,662 --> 00:07:03,381
What is it Heini,has she 
canceled that supper date?

129
00:07:03,381 --> 00:07:06,509
Oh,no as a matter of fact it was the

130
00:07:06,809 --> 00:07:07,836
Gestapo

131
00:07:09,604 --> 00:07:11,056
The want me there now

132
00:07:11,965 --> 00:07:12,974
It is something I

133
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:15,393
Probably a driving offense
or something like that

134
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:19,022
Expect I'll be back in 20 minutes

135
00:07:20,065 --> 00:07:23,360
In case I'm not in time,Happy New Year

136
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:59,729
One,two,three only four tonight,Sebastian

137
00:08:00,197 --> 00:08:01,439
I'm afraid so,Sir

138
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:03,024
Large Munchener

139
00:08:03,775 --> 00:08:04,775
Father

140
00:08:05,243 --> 00:08:06,444
-Emil
-Hello Karl

141
00:08:06,687 --> 00:08:08,144
Rudolf

142
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:11,366
I must say these reunions give me a 
slight sense of decreasing exhilaration

143
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:14,828
I never realized that this 
room was so large

144
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:17,122
Let's get rid of some of those chairs

145
00:08:18,673 --> 00:08:20,750
-Any news of Heini?
-No

146
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,169
No news

147
00:08:25,764 --> 00:08:26,798
Your beer,Sir

148
00:08:28,517 --> 00:08:31,094
Cheer up Sebastian take a drink with it

149
00:08:31,645 --> 00:08:33,346
Oh thank you very much,Sir

150
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:34,889
We are here anyway

151
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:38,018
Emil are your audiences still 
hanging on every word you sing?

152
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:39,936
I'm afraid not there's are words I sing

153
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:41,396
more likely to hang me

154
00:08:41,412 --> 00:08:42,564
Don't sing

155
00:08:43,023 --> 00:08:45,692
Some actors I know might 
be improved by hanging

156
00:08:46,435 --> 00:08:49,446
Really,Father,remember you 
thought that most unchristian sentiment

157
00:08:49,446 --> 00:08:50,446
Gentlemen

158
00:08:51,823 --> 00:08:52,823
Sebastian

159
00:08:57,128 --> 00:09:01,374
Gentlemen I didn't mean tell you 
until the end of the evening

160
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:04,878
But I'm afraid that this is our last night

161
00:09:05,971 --> 00:09:08,590
We have orders to close the whole club

162
00:09:10,508 --> 00:09:12,761
Student meeting are forbidden now Dr

163
00:09:13,803 --> 00:09:14,803
But I

164
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:20,018
I would like to say how much 
I've enjoyed serving you,gentlemen

165
00:09:41,539 --> 00:09:43,666
After that I don't think 
we can pretend anymore

166
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:47,670
No,what good are meeting places for friends

167
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:51,174
When one can't be sure any longer 
who is your friend,I'm going home

168
00:09:52,175 --> 00:09:54,010
-Good night,Father
-Good night,Emil

169
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:57,472
-Coming,Rudolph
-Yes-Good night,Karl

170
00:09:58,598 --> 00:09:59,598
Bye Emil

171
00:10:00,317 --> 00:10:02,769
Oh,I must be getting along to a church

172
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,980
You're coming to watch service,aren't you?

173
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:07,941
Yes I hope to bring my wife with me

174
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:09,651
If I can get her away from theater in time

175
00:10:09,651 --> 00:10:11,820
-Let's see she is playing in
-Iphigenia

176
00:10:12,362 --> 00:10:14,280
Oh yes of course

177
00:10:14,906 --> 00:10:15,906
Iphigenia

178
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:18,118
I should be glad if you'd come

179
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:24,374
There's nothing wrong,Father?

180
00:10:24,374 --> 00:10:26,167
No,no,nothing only

181
00:10:26,727 --> 00:10:28,378
I should just be glad if you could come

182
00:11:18,553 --> 00:11:20,388
-How much have you seen?
-Last act

183
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:24,017
-You are wonderful
-Oh wasn't very very bad

184
00:11:25,635 --> 00:11:27,478
The moment I saw the Fuhrer I collapsed

185
00:11:30,173 --> 00:11:31,191
She's just coming

186
00:11:32,325 --> 00:11:33,526
-Hello,Otto
-Hello

187
00:11:33,526 --> 00:11:34,777
You're rather quickly

188
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:36,112
I had I'm just staying on duty

189
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:39,574
-Very pretty
-What do you think of my sets?

190
00:11:39,574 --> 00:11:40,574
I liked them

191
00:11:40,641 --> 00:11:41,641
Me?

192
00:11:41,668 --> 00:11:42,744
You're all right

193
00:11:42,994 --> 00:11:43,994
You beast

194
00:11:44,046 --> 00:11:45,872
Actually I thought you were 
frightfully good

195
00:11:45,906 --> 00:11:47,415
Didn't you Hanna?

196
00:11:47,957 --> 00:11:48,958
I've seen her worse

197
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:50,168
Take a week's notice

198
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:52,962
The Fuhrer thought you were marvelous

199
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:54,242
How do you know?

200
00:11:54,288 --> 00:11:55,673
I was watching him the whole time

201
00:11:55,757 --> 00:11:57,266
You must found the play very exciting

202
00:11:58,101 --> 00:11:59,469
I can always see it again

203
00:11:59,928 --> 00:12:02,096
You know that uniform is very becoming

204
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:03,723
Glad you like it

205
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:07,435
I do indeed,have you've been 
doing any painting lately?

206
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:09,537
I haven't much time for 
that sort of things nowadays

207
00:12:09,579 --> 00:12:10,638
No I suppose not

208
00:12:11,489 --> 00:12:12,982
-Good night,Irena
-Good night,darling

209
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:15,443
-Good night Karl
-Good night Otto

210
00:12:16,786 --> 00:12:17,862
When the crowd comes in

211
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:19,889
you won't let them keep you 
for too long,will you?

212
00:12:19,889 --> 00:12:21,449
-No,of course not
-Give me one of those

213
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,033
Thank you

214
00:12:23,092 --> 00:12:24,410
-Do and get yourself a drink
-Yes

215
00:12:26,037 --> 00:12:27,747
Hanna,see who that is will you?

216
00:12:32,961 --> 00:12:33,961
Rabenau

217
00:12:34,012 --> 00:12:35,088
Ask him to come in

218
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:40,134
Willie,I'm glad to see you

219
00:12:41,511 --> 00:12:42,553
More wonderful than ever

220
00:12:42,553 --> 00:12:43,930
I was enchanted

221
00:12:45,098 --> 00:12:46,432
Good evening Roeder

222
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:48,059
I hope I'm not in the way

223
00:12:48,059 --> 00:12:50,186
No one could be more welcome

224
00:12:50,361 --> 00:12:51,479
Let me give you a drink

225
00:12:52,814 --> 00:12:54,607
On this occasion I think I must

226
00:12:57,452 --> 00:13:00,697
Actually this is an official visit 
but we must just drink a toast

227
00:13:01,489 --> 00:13:03,866
The new director of popular patron

228
00:13:04,918 --> 00:13:08,997
Our most distinguished actress 
and producer,Frau Irena Roeder

229
00:13:14,085 --> 00:13:15,085
You

230
00:13:17,547 --> 00:13:18,715
You mean me?

231
00:13:20,675 --> 00:13:21,675
But

232
00:13:22,535 --> 00:13:23,594
I can't believe it

233
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:26,180
Karl,did you hear what he said?

234
00:13:26,973 --> 00:13:28,558
Aren't you drinking the toast?

235
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:31,853
To you my darling

236
00:13:34,347 --> 00:13:35,356
Taken my breath away

237
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:38,359
Der fuhrer wants to 
congratulate you himself

238
00:13:38,359 --> 00:13:40,528
I'm here to take you to 
the chancellery at once

239
00:13:40,870 --> 00:13:42,739
Of course I'll be as quick as I can

240
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:46,284
There's a whole crowd of them 
outside,you have to see them

241
00:13:46,284 --> 00:13:48,786
Oh dear,I'm afraid I must

242
00:13:48,953 --> 00:13:50,371
Give me a minute

243
00:13:51,631 --> 00:13:53,708
I'll be waiting for you in the car,Irena

244
00:13:59,797 --> 00:14:01,716
We'll have to celebrate our 
new year tomorrow

245
00:14:02,425 --> 00:14:04,135
Oh,darling I am sorry

246
00:14:04,594 --> 00:14:06,429
-What could I do
-Never mind

247
00:14:06,821 --> 00:14:09,040
You'll be able to meet Father 
Landbach some other time

248
00:14:09,140 --> 00:14:10,174
You're going anyway?

249
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:13,186
Otherwise he'll be brokenhearted

250
00:14:16,397 --> 00:14:18,858
-I'll be thinking of you at midnight
-Oh,darling

251
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:22,987
Hanna,you let them in

252
00:14:25,907 --> 00:14:27,241
Oh,good evening,Dr Roeder

253
00:14:27,442 --> 00:14:32,080
My dear you were divine my husband 
stayed away from staff to see you

254
00:15:07,749 --> 00:15:09,534
My dear brethren

255
00:15:09,534 --> 00:15:12,161
Before I begin my address this evening

256
00:15:12,161 --> 00:15:14,705
I want to tell you of something

257
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:20,044
something which I'm afraid will 
distress you as it has distressed me

258
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:23,548
our good friend Father Brandt

259
00:15:24,715 --> 00:15:29,804
who is well known to
and loved by many of us

260
00:15:29,804 --> 00:15:34,058
has been removed from his parish

261
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:45,069
It is said that he was an 
enemy of the Reich

262
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:50,074
A phrase we've lately heard 
used of many of our brethren

263
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:54,662
but one which we who knew him best

264
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:58,458
will I think find it difficult to believe

265
00:16:00,535 --> 00:16:04,088
I intend to ask you 
prayers for Father Brandt

266
00:16:04,330 --> 00:16:05,882
But before I do so

267
00:16:06,757 --> 00:16:10,052
I feel it my duty to 
give any who may wish

268
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:13,347
the opportunity of leaving now

269
00:16:30,581 --> 00:16:34,535
I am glad so many of you will 
give him a benefit of your prayers

270
00:16:38,623 --> 00:16:40,166
He is in need of them

271
00:16:42,051 --> 00:16:44,629
In asking our Mighty God to protect him

272
00:16:44,629 --> 00:16:45,755
Shut up and come on down

273
00:16:45,755 --> 00:16:52,053
I would ask you to intercede also 
for those others who have preceded him

274
00:16:52,053 --> 00:16:53,137
Stop him,come down

275
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:55,004
Friz Felderberg Johann Schmalz

276
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,670
Clear the church

277
00:16:58,434 --> 00:16:59,434
Heinrich Meindorf

278
00:16:59,527 --> 00:17:00,527
Emil Sonbach

279
00:17:01,646 --> 00:17:02,646
Hans Feldman

280
00:17:03,356 --> 00:17:04,356
Oscar Brandt

281
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:06,274
Fritz Schulz

282
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:08,563
Friedrich Mann

283
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:09,694
Herman Geldt

284
00:17:11,656 --> 00:17:16,244
for those I have named I have asked 
for blessing of our heavenly Father

285
00:17:22,242 --> 00:17:23,709
Come along hurry up clear the church

286
00:17:32,752 --> 00:17:34,220
Come on you get out

287
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:54,574
All right Hanna,good night,
see you in the morning

288
00:17:58,119 --> 00:18:00,121
It wasn't nearly so alarming as I expected

289
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:03,207
He was most enthusiastic 
about the performance

290
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:04,917
He couldn't have been more kind

291
00:18:05,793 --> 00:18:09,171
Everyone was there,Goring and his 
wife and nearly all party leaders

292
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:12,550
I can have my own offices 
and all the staff I want

293
00:18:12,550 --> 00:18:13,926
Are you listening?

294
00:18:15,036 --> 00:18:16,053
Yes,of course

295
00:18:17,054 --> 00:18:19,557
My first thing is Stuttgart 
just think what a city

296
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:23,019
Any producer would give his soul 
for let lose on a job like that

297
00:18:23,019 --> 00:18:26,314
Apparently there is to be no restrictions 
as regards expenses or labor

298
00:18:28,316 --> 00:18:29,734
I've been thinking that it'll be

299
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:33,237
Darling,you're not listening

300
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:36,531
What's the matter?

301
00:18:37,583 --> 00:18:41,621
I'm sorry,my sweet,I saw something 
this evening which upsets me rather

302
00:18:42,613 --> 00:18:43,664
Of what?

303
00:18:43,664 --> 00:18:48,419
Oh,just a boy I used to 
know behaving horribly

304
00:18:48,470 --> 00:18:49,562
Who?

305
00:18:50,446 --> 00:18:53,424
Let's not talk about it,on with 
what you were saying

306
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:57,053
I hardly know what I am saying

307
00:18:58,512 --> 00:18:59,805
I can't believe it

308
00:19:00,806 --> 00:19:02,516
I can quite believe it myself

309
00:19:03,434 --> 00:19:04,852
You are pleased though,aren't you?

310
00:19:05,586 --> 00:19:06,646
You want me to be?

311
00:19:08,339 --> 00:19:09,398
Oh,of course I do

312
00:19:09,498 --> 00:19:11,233
The only thing that matters

313
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:12,443
Then you go ahead

314
00:19:13,244 --> 00:19:16,864
A few more people like you at the 
head of things,we might be a lot better off

315
00:19:17,198 --> 00:19:18,282
Oh dear

316
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:20,201
Sounds very solemn

317
00:19:20,201 --> 00:19:24,288
Being married to a high government 
official is a very solemn business

318
00:19:31,479 --> 00:19:32,479
Karl

319
00:19:35,049 --> 00:19:37,677
This job won't make any 
difference between us

320
00:19:39,662 --> 00:19:40,721
Of course not

321
00:19:44,308 --> 00:19:45,851
And subversive remarks from the pulpit

322
00:19:45,851 --> 00:19:48,104
so inflamed the congregation 
the priest was injured

323
00:19:48,104 --> 00:19:49,104
Fatally

324
00:19:49,271 --> 00:19:51,982
Fortunately stormtroopers 
were able to restore order

325
00:19:51,982 --> 00:19:54,068
But it is evident that scrupulous agitators

326
00:19:54,068 --> 00:19:56,445
can no longer depend on their 
cloth to protect them

327
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:58,114
from the indignation of the people

328
00:19:59,115 --> 00:20:00,658
And here is the actual report,Sir

329
00:20:00,917 --> 00:20:02,743
They went too far and 
accidentally killed him

330
00:20:02,743 --> 00:20:05,162
A little overenthusiastic

331
00:20:05,755 --> 00:20:07,957
It is evident that unscrupulous agitators

332
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:12,002
can no longer depend on 
their cloth to protect them

333
00:20:12,002 --> 00:20:14,797
from the indignation of the people

334
00:20:17,049 --> 00:20:18,551
Landbach's epitaph

335
00:20:20,928 --> 00:20:22,221
He'll get no more

336
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:25,516
And we are responsible

337
00:20:25,575 --> 00:20:26,475
We?

338
00:20:26,517 --> 00:20:28,811
People like us criticizing,
grumbling and doing nothing

339
00:20:28,945 --> 00:20:30,396
We are stifled my friend

340
00:20:30,396 --> 00:20:31,731
What can we do?

341
00:20:31,731 --> 00:20:34,734
Still people with a sense of decency 
like you and Fenner

342
00:20:34,734 --> 00:20:38,112
there must be others if 
we could only reach them

343
00:20:38,838 --> 00:20:39,905
Who's that?

344
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:41,666
I don't know

345
00:20:46,487 --> 00:20:47,538
What are you doing?

346
00:20:48,172 --> 00:20:50,040
Sorry,Sir didn't think I'd disturb you

347
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:53,753
You could hear us in the 
next room,couldn't you?

348
00:20:53,753 --> 00:20:54,753
No,Sir

349
00:20:54,837 --> 00:20:57,005
Why are you here there's 
nothing wrong with the radio?

350
00:20:57,005 --> 00:20:58,649
Just an ordinary routine inspection,Sir

351
00:20:58,649 --> 00:20:59,717
It's all in order

352
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:00,800
I see

353
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:02,720
Quite an interesting job yours

354
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:04,180
And well paid

355
00:21:04,922 --> 00:21:06,390
I don't know so much about that,Sir

356
00:21:07,483 --> 00:21:09,393
I do manage to pick up 
a little bit on the side

357
00:21:09,610 --> 00:21:10,644
Doing what?

358
00:21:11,604 --> 00:21:13,564
Help a friend of mine 
build sets in the evening

359
00:21:13,939 --> 00:21:15,316
A budding Marconi

360
00:21:15,316 --> 00:21:16,901
Wish I was,Sir

361
00:21:17,727 --> 00:21:19,904
I think he was about the greatest 
man who ever lived

362
00:21:21,205 --> 00:21:23,491
You know,I shouldn't let the 
Gestapo hear you say that

363
00:21:25,334 --> 00:21:26,452
I didn't mean anything

364
00:21:27,528 --> 00:21:28,996
You won't say anything,Sir,will you

365
00:21:28,996 --> 00:21:31,540
You see I've been trying to 
get license to build sets on my own

366
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:33,709
well it's hard enough unless you got a pull

367
00:21:33,709 --> 00:21:34,877
Starting up yourself?

368
00:21:34,877 --> 00:21:36,170
I want to,Sir,yes

369
00:21:36,370 --> 00:21:37,463
You're a married man?

370
00:21:37,563 --> 00:21:39,006
Going to be,next month,Sir

371
00:21:39,006 --> 00:21:41,467
I might be able to put in a 
word for you for that license

372
00:21:41,467 --> 00:21:42,747
Thank you,Sir

373
00:21:42,835 --> 00:21:44,253
-Whats your name?
-Hans Glaser,Sir

374
00:21:44,253 --> 00:21:46,388
Al right,you drop me a 
line tell me all about it

375
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:47,388
Yes,Sir

376
00:21:47,448 --> 00:21:48,908
-Thank you,Sir,good morning
-Good bye

377
00:21:53,687 --> 00:21:55,314
There's one they haven't spoiled

378
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:56,440
-Yes
-Yes

379
00:21:56,457 --> 00:21:57,791
But it's a nice thing we decided

380
00:21:57,791 --> 00:22:00,653
that an ordinary workman could not 
scare us out of our lives

381
00:22:11,689 --> 00:22:12,915
-Hello Fritz
-Good morning,Hans

382
00:22:12,982 --> 00:22:14,174
Give me half a dozen,will you

383
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:29,514
Hey

384
00:22:30,174 --> 00:22:32,685
-Hans,someone might see us
-Who cares

385
00:22:32,685 --> 00:22:34,520
-Elly,I've got some wonderful news 
-What?

386
00:22:35,337 --> 00:22:36,730
No,I don't think you ought to know

387
00:22:36,730 --> 00:22:38,107
Oh,please,please tell me

388
00:22:38,107 --> 00:22:39,116
All right,listen

389
00:22:40,150 --> 00:22:42,278
Elly,here you are children

390
00:22:42,278 --> 00:22:43,863
A nice hot lunch

391
00:22:43,863 --> 00:22:46,615
Sausages,potatoes and sauerkraut

392
00:22:46,699 --> 00:22:48,075
You shouldn't have bothered

393
00:22:48,075 --> 00:22:50,085
Something colder could have 
been quite good enough

394
00:22:50,085 --> 00:22:52,037
Rubbish,you won't feeding up

395
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:53,247
Well I can't stay,Elly

396
00:22:53,247 --> 00:22:55,666
I've got lot's to,and I don't 
like leaving the flat too long

397
00:22:55,666 --> 00:22:58,586
with that wretched Frau Lehman 
nosing about like she does

398
00:22:58,586 --> 00:23:00,671
Do you know I think that woman is actually

399
00:23:00,671 --> 00:23:02,339
capable of raiding our larder

400
00:23:02,339 --> 00:23:04,592
-Nonsense granny
-Oh yes she is

401
00:23:04,592 --> 00:23:07,303
I've got some very special for you tonight

402
00:23:07,303 --> 00:23:09,638
-Don't you be late either of you
-We won't-Good bye

403
00:23:09,638 --> 00:23:10,714
Good bye,granny

404
00:23:10,714 --> 00:23:12,266
Come on you must tell me

405
00:23:12,266 --> 00:23:14,476
-Guess whom I've been just talking to?
-No,who?

406
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:18,147
-Have you London Times please?
-I'm sorry,Sir,it's been confiscated today

407
00:23:18,147 --> 00:23:19,565
What again?

408
00:23:21,609 --> 00:23:22,860
Now tell me who was it?

409
00:23:22,860 --> 00:23:23,861
Doctor Karl Roeder

410
00:23:23,861 --> 00:23:24,987
The great specialist

411
00:23:24,987 --> 00:23:26,055
-No
-Yes

412
00:23:26,055 --> 00:23:28,699
What's more he's going to 
get me a radio sales license

413
00:23:28,699 --> 00:23:30,075
Hans,that's wonderful

414
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:31,368
I should think it is

415
00:23:32,470 --> 00:23:33,537
We can get get married

416
00:23:36,374 --> 00:23:37,374
Right away

417
00:23:42,129 --> 00:23:43,839
I'll make the finest sets on the market

418
00:23:45,115 --> 00:23:46,425
You'll have a real diamond ring

419
00:23:47,893 --> 00:23:49,345
Yes I had a long talk with Roeder

420
00:23:49,345 --> 00:23:51,180
He asked my opinion of all sort of things

421
00:23:51,180 --> 00:23:52,180
Not really?

422
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:54,725
Yes he was most impressed

423
00:23:56,518 --> 00:23:59,146
You know when a chap is 
seen with people like Roeder

424
00:24:00,114 --> 00:24:01,273
It's nothing we can't do

425
00:24:01,273 --> 00:24:04,193
We might even control the world's radio

426
00:24:04,410 --> 00:24:06,528
Hans,I think you're wonderful

427
00:24:10,508 --> 00:24:12,368
Watch one now for Hans 
flight,see you tonight

428
00:24:12,368 --> 00:24:13,368
Good bye

429
00:24:34,799 --> 00:24:37,518
-Good afternoon,Frau Schmidt
-Good afternoon,Frau Lehman

430
00:24:37,518 --> 00:24:40,279
I suppose you haven't got
a bit lard in that bag,Frau Schmidt

431
00:24:40,362 --> 00:24:41,689
-No I have not
-Oh,Frau Schmidt

432
00:24:43,107 --> 00:24:44,441
-Just a tiny,please
-No

433
00:24:44,441 --> 00:24:46,527
You had all of mine last week

434
00:24:47,027 --> 00:24:48,047
That's it,is it?

435
00:24:48,112 --> 00:24:49,646
Living on the fat of the land

436
00:24:49,705 --> 00:24:51,540
and you can't grant me 
a little piece of lard

437
00:24:51,607 --> 00:24:54,368
See your neighbour starve would
you never raise a finger to help her?

438
00:24:54,368 --> 00:24:55,377
Now look here

439
00:24:55,377 --> 00:24:57,387
You know very well I've no lard to give you

440
00:24:57,387 --> 00:25:00,933
after all you've got as much as to 
spend on food as I have as you didn't

441
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:04,686
-Well,out with it
-Well,spend it differently

442
00:25:04,786 --> 00:25:07,164
So,now I can't have a drop 
or two to keep my strength up

443
00:25:07,164 --> 00:25:09,708
You let me starve in the gutter,I suppose

444
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:11,885
Because Judgment you're asking for

445
00:25:13,095 --> 00:25:14,304
The Judgment

446
00:25:15,856 --> 00:25:18,017
What a type that hag

447
00:25:19,184 --> 00:25:20,184
My lard

448
00:25:22,896 --> 00:25:24,356
"Mightiest nation in the world"

449
00:25:25,524 --> 00:25:28,986
"Our great fuhrer as given 
us new hope and a new faith"

450
00:25:29,528 --> 00:25:32,364
"and Germany's destiny 
will be the world's destiny"

451
00:25:52,301 --> 00:25:54,928
"On est entendre Fleur 
du mal tango de Brazil"

452
00:25:54,928 --> 00:26:00,559
"et maintenant,chere auditeur
 vous ecoutez a passe de muse quickstep"

453
00:26:22,172 --> 00:26:23,290
You see what did I tell you

454
00:26:23,457 --> 00:26:25,626
-All listening to foreign stations
-Shut up

455
00:26:26,085 --> 00:26:29,546
"vous ecoutez maintenant une 
autre information Washington.."

456
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:34,968
But I haven't heard 
anything it was just the music

457
00:26:38,931 --> 00:26:40,849
You seem to follow foreign broadcast

458
00:26:45,404 --> 00:26:47,272
-Take her away
-Oh no

459
00:26:47,689 --> 00:26:49,566
No please just a moment

460
00:26:49,566 --> 00:26:53,362
I can explain,don't you understand 
I was only listening to the music

461
00:26:53,362 --> 00:26:55,322
I wasn’t do anything,oh Elly

462
00:26:55,322 --> 00:26:57,699
Granny they're taking you

463
00:26:57,825 --> 00:26:58,909
Who are you?

464
00:27:01,370 --> 00:27:03,956
She's my granny what's been happening

465
00:27:04,706 --> 00:27:07,000
What's the matter,where are they taking her

466
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:10,011
Quite calm,listen,there's nothing to 
worry about,just a matter of routine

467
00:27:10,496 --> 00:27:13,423
We'll take her to the police station,
where she'll answer a few questions

468
00:27:14,091 --> 00:27:15,551
She'll be back in an hour

469
00:27:16,051 --> 00:27:17,719
Now if you want to help your grandma

470
00:27:20,222 --> 00:27:22,724
This is would you could do it,
tell me a little about her

471
00:27:38,140 --> 00:27:40,350
Hello darling I thought you 
were going out to Grunewald

472
00:27:41,243 --> 00:27:42,536
I got Ludwig to go for me

473
00:27:43,495 --> 00:27:45,247
So I could spend a little time with you

474
00:27:45,247 --> 00:27:46,498
Thank you,darling

475
00:27:47,383 --> 00:27:49,710
There's a wagon load of 
fan mail for you over there

476
00:27:50,127 --> 00:27:53,422
I look at it presently for just 
two minutes I want to look at you

477
00:27:56,717 --> 00:27:58,552
-What sort of morning?
-Wonderful

478
00:28:00,454 --> 00:28:03,307
Now I'm married to the Reichsdirector 
of Popular Pageantry

479
00:28:03,307 --> 00:28:05,267
I could have charged double fees

480
00:28:06,476 --> 00:28:07,836
You remember this

481
00:28:29,366 --> 00:28:30,792
Sorry I can't dine with you tonight

482
00:28:30,792 --> 00:28:32,794
-Oh hello
-I'm just going on duty

483
00:28:32,794 --> 00:28:34,421
You're always going on duty

484
00:28:34,421 --> 00:28:35,505
What is it this time?

485
00:28:35,505 --> 00:28:37,216
-Just cleaning up
-Cleaning up?

486
00:28:38,133 --> 00:28:39,968
-Like the other evening
-What do you mean?

487
00:28:40,928 --> 00:28:41,928
Ask Otto

488
00:28:42,146 --> 00:28:43,597
I do my duty and obey orders

489
00:28:43,597 --> 00:28:45,432
Even when duties mean smashing up churches

490
00:28:45,432 --> 00:28:46,925
and beating various people to death

491
00:28:47,351 --> 00:28:50,062
He was an enemy of the state 
even if he was friend of yours

492
00:28:50,062 --> 00:28:52,648
But his death was an accident

493
00:28:52,665 --> 00:28:53,690
Was it?

494
00:28:54,491 --> 00:28:57,069
Does it occur to you that 
he was doing his duty too

495
00:28:57,319 --> 00:28:59,321
Duty? His duty was to his state

496
00:29:00,164 --> 00:29:01,573
Not to his conscience?

497
00:29:01,665 --> 00:29:04,842
If it wasn't for your position he would 
be put away for saying less than that?

498
00:29:04,877 --> 00:29:06,686
-You are just...
-Otto I'd better think you go

499
00:29:11,708 --> 00:29:12,709
What was all that about?

500
00:29:13,036 --> 00:29:15,921
The time they'll finished with him 
he'll have no more soul than a sheep

501
00:29:15,980 --> 00:29:18,907
You've seen what's happening to him 
it's happening to thousands like him

502
00:29:18,916 --> 00:29:22,427
Blind obedience for a rule 
of force and terrorism

503
00:29:22,427 --> 00:29:23,427
Frightening

504
00:29:24,129 --> 00:29:25,222
What has Otto done?

505
00:29:26,215 --> 00:29:28,100
He's the boy I told you 
about the other evening

506
00:29:29,168 --> 00:29:30,852
He was in the raid on Landbach's church

507
00:29:31,712 --> 00:29:33,313
He was only obeying his orders

508
00:29:33,313 --> 00:29:34,373
Oh,no he wasn't

509
00:29:35,565 --> 00:29:38,860
I was there I saw the look on his face

510
00:29:38,860 --> 00:29:41,029
He was enjoying himself

511
00:29:42,239 --> 00:29:45,450
But if,it was the congregation 
that attacked Landbach

512
00:29:49,288 --> 00:29:51,164
Do you really believe that?

513
00:29:56,445 --> 00:29:57,462
Hello

514
00:29:58,797 --> 00:29:59,797
Who?

515
00:30:00,424 --> 00:30:01,883
Oh yes I remember

516
00:30:08,015 --> 00:30:09,015
What's the address?

517
00:30:09,725 --> 00:30:11,018
Right,I'll come along

518
00:30:12,811 --> 00:30:14,438
Sorry,Irena,I have to go

519
00:30:16,198 --> 00:30:17,399
Something rather serious

520
00:30:19,985 --> 00:30:20,985
Irena

521
00:30:23,480 --> 00:30:24,865
I'd like you to do something

522
00:30:25,315 --> 00:30:26,867
I'd like you to come with me

523
00:30:29,077 --> 00:30:30,078
You might be able to help

524
00:30:32,756 --> 00:30:34,166
It's a young girl

525
00:30:35,417 --> 00:30:37,586
Well,of course I will

526
00:30:38,545 --> 00:30:40,130
